    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "Parents should not forget their childhood years, how much they yearned for sympathy and love, and how unhappy they felt when censured and fretfully chided. They should be young again in their feelings, and bring their minds down to understand the wants of their children.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">4<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"1T 387.1\" data-link=\"116.1845\">Testimonies for the Church 1:387, 388</span>.</span></a></sup>",
