    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>Reasonable Desires to Be Gratified</strong>&mdash;You should ever impress upon your children the fact that you love them; that you are laboring for their interest; that their happiness is dear to you; and that you design to do only <span class=\"page-break\" data-page=\"198\"></span> that which is for their good. You should gratify their little wants whenever you can reasonably do so.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">10<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"4T 140.1\" data-link=\"114.721\">Testimonies for the Church 4:140</span>.</span></a></sup>",
